JOHANNESURG – Asset manager, Benguela, says it sent a letter questioning Capitec Bank's process around the rescheduling of loans. It said the letter was sent two weeks before the Viceroy report was released. The firm says its analysis of Capitec's financials shows that the bank's solvency is not a concern, but it does question Capitec's business practices. READ: Viceroy report riddled with inaccuracies, says Capitec Benguela says Viceroy's call for the bank to be placed under curatorship is reckless. Capitec says it will respond to Benguela's concerns. eNCA